d raises the still controversial issue of how we decide what embryos mean.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEmbryology, HumanxSocial aspects. 0aHuman reproductive technologyxSocial aspects. 0aMedical anthropology. 0aTissue culturexSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  a20th century american history.  a20th century scientific history.  abaltimore foundling homes.  abiology.  acarnegie institute of washington.  aembryo babies.  aembryo collection.  aembryo production factory.  aembryology.  afetal politics.  agertrude stein.  ahealthcare.  aicons of life.  ajohns hopkins anatomy department.  amaternal politics.  amedial treatment.  amedical care.  amount holyoke collection.  aourselves unborn.  apregnancy.  apregnant women.  ascience.  ascientific study.  asocial artifacts.  aspecimen collecting.  aunited states of america.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094472540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944725423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944725/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles